    "Cross-school teaching research and exchanges can promote the sharing of high-quality educational courses and results in the same region.",
    "Incorporating quality education activities into school assessments can strengthen accountability and encourage active participation in reform.",
    "However, there are still some challenges to overcome.",
    "Comprehensive training is needed for educators to address their perceptions.",
    "Adequate resources are necessary, and appropriate evaluation mechanisms need to be established among participants to monitor the progress and effectiveness of the reform."
